    <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">Hints</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-700 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>Use Python's <code class="text-stone-900 bg-stone-200/70 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">csv.DictReader</code> and <code class="text-stone-900 bg-stone-200/70 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">csv.DictWriter</code> to read and write CSVs by column name.</li>
        <li>The <code class="text-stone-900 bg-stone-200/70 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">name</code> field will look like <code class="text-stone-900 bg-stone-200/70 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">"Abbott, Hannah"</code>. Split on <code class="text-stone-900 bg-stone-200/70 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">", "</code> to get last and first name separately.</li>
        <li>Wrap your file open calls in <code class="text-stone-900 bg-stone-200/70 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">try / except FileNotFoundError</code> to handle a missing input file gracefully.</li>
        <li>Remember to call <code class="text-stone-900 bg-stone-200/70 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">writer.writeheader()</code> before writing rows.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

## How to Test Your Code

Does your code work as prescribed when:

- `before.csv` exists with several rows?
- `before.csv` does not exist?
- A name contains only one part (no comma)?

